## 9. Summary of Key Factors Influencing Favorable Dividends for Common Stockholders

| Factor                      | Description                                                                                     | Effect on Dividend Favorability                      |
|-----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| Profitability               | Ability to generate consistent and growing earnings                                            | Higher profitability → higher and stable dividends  |
| Capital Needs               | Requirement to retain earnings for growth and investment                                       | High capital needs → lower dividends                 |
| Liquidity                   | Availability of cash to pay dividends                                                          | Strong liquidity → reliable dividend payments        |
| Investor Expectations       | Preferences for income vs. capital gains                                                       | Income-oriented investors → pressure for dividends   |
| Legal/Institutional Factors | Restrictions on dividend payments and financing options                                       | Constraints may limit dividends                       |
| Macroeconomic Factors       | Inflation and interest rates affecting costs and investor demands                              | Inflation may suppress dividends; interest rates impact cost of capital |
| Company Size and Maturity   | Larger, mature firms tend to pay dividends; smaller firms retain earnings                       | Mature firms → more favorable dividends              |
| Dividend Trends             | Historical dividend stability and growth                                                      | Positive trends encourage continued favorable dividends |

